text: Intelligent investors understand that process supersedes the comedy of sound bytes that traders often see in the business media. Smart traders/investors recognize that if you are on the playing field you make mistakes -unlike the many (shrouded in anonymity) that sweep mistakes

under the carpet to appear "smart," or others that try increase their viewership or to sell a service . Real trader/investors understand risk control/management and the folly of one factor decision making. Bonafide trader/investors are in for the long term, not for the week.
That is why I have subscribed to @hedgeye @KeithMcCullough I want valuable, untainted, honest, risk-based input. @threadreaderapp unroll
